## Vercel Web Analytics Implementation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for the Joinspire Studios website.

### Changes Made

**1. Package Installation**
- Installed `@vercel/analytics@^2.0.1` package using npm
- Updated package.json and package-lock.json accordingly

**2. Code Integration**
- Modified `src/App.jsx` to add Vercel Analytics:
  - Added import: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/react";`
  - Added `<Analytics />` component inside the ThemeWrap component, just before the closing tag
  - This ensures analytics tracking is active across all pages (home, service pages, and client pages)

### Implementation Details

Following the official Vercel Analytics documentation for React/Vite applications, I:
1. Fetched the latest documentation from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart
2. Identified the correct integration method for React + Vite projects
3. Used the React-specific package (`@vercel/analytics/react`)
4. Placed the Analytics component at the root level to track all page views and interactions

### Testing

- ✅ Build completed successfully (`npm run build`)
- ✅ No errors or warnings introduced
- ✅ All existing functionality preserved
- ✅ Analytics component properly integrated into the component tree

### Next Steps

Once deployed to Vercel, analytics will automatically begin collecting data. You can:
1. View analytics in the Vercel dashboard under the Analytics tab
2. Analytics will track page views, web vitals, and user interactions
3. No additional configuration needed - it works out of the box

The analytics implementation is production-ready and will start tracking visitors as soon as the changes are deployed.
